  "text": "Calcium homeostasis: An increase in intracellular calcium levels is associated with sepsis-induced brain injury. [CITATION_1] Zhan et al. demonstrated that hippocampal intracellular calcium levels were increased after CLP in rats. [CITATION_2] This increase could be related to ischemia, the presence of excitatory amino acids or a direct effect of cytokines. Altered calcium levels may alter neurotransmitter levels and impair learning, memory and cognitive function in septic patients.",
